-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Medical errors claim the lives of over a quarter million people in the US each year.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Medical error is the third leading cause of fatalities in the US, just behind heart disease and cancer.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Each of us will likely experience a meaningful diagnostic error in our lifetime.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Diagnostic errors are increasing as the delivery of health care increases in complexity.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>5% of U.S. adults who seek outpatient care each year experience a diagnostic error.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Diagnostic errors contribute to approximately 10% of preventable patient deaths.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Diagnostic errors account for up to 17% of hospital adverse events.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Diagnostic errors are the leading type of paid medical malpractice claims.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The average US hospital pays out more than $300 million each year in malpractice settlements.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Among medical errors, diagnostic errors are almost twice as likely to result in patient death..</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns --></div></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:verdure/home-did-you-know -->\n\n<!-- wp:verdure/vdslider {\"hasNavigation\":true,\"hasLoop\":true,\"maxDesktopItems\":\"3\",\"className\":\"vdslider\\u002d\\u002dhornetbox\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-verdure-vdslider vdslider vdslider--has-navigation vdslider--has-loop vdslider--hornetbox\" data-spacebetween=\"20\" data-maxitems=\"3\"><div class=\"container\"><div class=\"testimonial-heading\"><p>TESTIMONIALS</p><h2>What Our Customer Say!</h2><